//
// SmolLM2-1.7B compile-only smoke test: builds every prefill + decode kernel
// ELF through the AIR -> AIE -> aiecc -> Peano pipeline. No NPU dispatch and
// no HuggingFace weight download.
//
// NOT CI-triggered by design: the filename intentionally OMITS "peano", so the
// CI peano suite (`lit --filter "peano"`, see
// programming_examples/CMakeLists.txt check-programming-examples-peano) does not
// collect it. llama32_1b's compile lit is the bf16 prefill/decode CI signal;
// SmolLM2 shares the same shared/builders + shared/infra assembly, so a second
// always-on compile job would add CI time for little extra coverage. This lit
// is kept so the example is runnable on demand:
//   lit -v programming_examples/llms/smollm2_1_7b/run_npu2_compile.lit
//
// Gated on ryzen_ai_npu2 because the shared builders hardcode the AIE2P target
// (shared/infra/external_kernels.py --target=aie2p-none-unknown-elf,
// shared/builders/gemm_builder.py arch="aie2p"). The compile does not touch the
// NPU device, so any NPU2-capable runner is sufficient.
//
// REQUIRES: ryzen_ai_npu2, peano
//
// RUN: mkdir -p test_peano_compile
// RUN: cd test_peano_compile
// RUN: make -f %S/Makefile clean
// RUN: make -f %S/Makefile compile PEANO_INSTALL_DIR=%PEANO_INSTALL_DIR | FileCheck %s
// CHECK: Compilation passed.
